---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy — PlainHireCheck" description="PlainHireCheck privacy policy — how we handle your data, cookies, and advertising."
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Home', href: '/' }, { name: 'Privacy Policy' }]}>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-[var(--color-muted)]">Last updated: January 15, 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>PlainHireCheck collects minimal data. We use privacy-focused analytics (Umami) that does not use cookies and does not collect personally identifiable information. We track page views, referral sources, and device types in aggregate form only.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Cookies & Tracking Technologies</h2>
      <p>PlainHireCheck does not set first-party cookies. However, third-party services used on this site may set cookies:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
        <li><strong>Google AdSense</strong> uses cookies to serve ads based on your visits to this and other websites.</li>
        <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> may set security cookies (e.g., <code>__cf_bm</code>) to distinguish humans from bots.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics (GA4)</strong> uses cookies to measure website traffic and usage patterns.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Your browser's light/dark theme preference is stored in localStorage, which never leaves your device.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Advertising</h2>
      <p>We display advertisements through <strong>Google AdSense</strong>. Google and its advertising partners may use cookies and web beacons to serve ads based on your prior visits to this and other websites.</p>
      <p>You can opt out of personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Data Sources</h2>
      <p>All data displayed on this site comes from state licensing boards, NCSL, and NASCLA — public government sources. No private or personally identifiable information is stored or displayed.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Third-Party Services</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
        <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — CDN, security, and hosting</li>
        <li><strong>Google AdSense</strong> — advertising</li>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — traffic measurement</li>
        <li><strong>Umami</strong> — privacy-focused, cookie-free analytics</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Under GDPR, CCPA, and similar privacy regulations, you have the right to know what data is collected, request deletion, and opt out of personalized advertising. California residents may opt out under CCPA.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>PlainHireCheck does not knowingly collect information from children under 13.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about this privacy policy: <a href="mailto:privacy@plainhirecheck.com" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline">privacy@plainhirecheck.com</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
